    "headline": "MLB Daily Recap - April 11, 2026",
    "article": "**Phillies Outlast Diamondbacks in Thrilling Finale**\n\nThe Philadelphia Phillies edged the Arizona Diamondbacks 4-3, with Kyle Schwarber and Bryce Harper delivering crucial hits. Ketel Marte's 2-run homer in the 7th inning tied the game for Arizona, but Harper's go-ahead single in the 9th sealed the win. On the mound, Taijuan Walker limited the Diamondbacks to 3 runs over 6 innings, while Brandon Pfaadt took the loss for Arizona.\n\nIn other games, the Detroit Tigers dominated the Miami Marlins 6-1 behind a strong team effort, with Otto Lopez and Riley Greene combining for 3 hits and 2 RBIs. The Pittsburgh Pirates also took down the Chicago Cubs 4-3, with Oneil Cruz and Bryan Reynolds leading the charge.",
